A HUB Thanksgiving!!!
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Come join the Hub Bay Area community in celebrating Thanksgiving! Please join us at the HUB San Francisco the evening of Monday November 5th for great food, music, and community. The illustrious chef Tim West will be preparing a delicious meal for all in attendance following a traditional Thanksgiving theme. New Addition!!! - Levi Felix and Brooke Dean from THE DIGITAL DETOX will be relieving you of your technology with their "phone-check station" and helping us set the intention for a meal full of gratitude, presence, and a good time off-the-grid. Musicical Feature - Chicken Paw Musical Feature - Bear Kittay Open jam session at the end of the evening - bring an instrument! This event is open to everyone. You don't have to be a HUB member, although joining the HUB is certainly encouraged! Menu: Local Roast Turkey Quinoa Stuffed Acorn Squash Vegetable Stuffing Country Gravy Cranberry Mint Sauce Garlic Mashed Potatoes Brussel Sprouts Kendall Jackson Wine $40 ticket includes dinner, drinks, and music. Responding to this facebook event by clicking that you are attending does not mean that you are registered!! Please register and pay here: http://hubthanksgiving.eventbrite.com/

USNC UN Women: Screening of "Honor Diaries" Followed by an In-Depth Discussion with Amy Logan and Raheel Raza
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Please come and join us for a screening of the award winning documentary "Honor Diaries," followed by a discussion with Amy Logan and Raheel Raza. Amy Logan is a global women’s human rights activist, speaker on violence against women, independent scholar on honor violence, and author of "The Seven Perfumes of Sacrifice." Raheel Raza is featured in "Honor Diaries" and is President of The Council for Muslims Facing Tomorrow. She is also the author of the book "Their Jihad – Not My Jihad" and is an activist for human rights, gender equality, and dignity in diversity. She is recipient of the Queen Elizabeth II Diamond Jubilee medal for service to Canada. The event will start at 6:30 p.m. It will be an opportunity to meet other people passionate about women's empowerment and human rights. Please RSVP at https://honorviolence.eventbrite.com. We hope to see you there! More information about "Honor Diaries" can be found here: http://www.honordiaries.com/ More about our organization: UN Women is the United Nations program tasked with advancing women’s rights and development around the world. We are committed to expanding support and raising funds within the United States for UN Women. We work in the SF Bay Area to raise awareness about the women's rights issues facing our world and local community. If interested in learning more, please send us an email at sanfranbayarea@unwomen-usnc.org.
